1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 c5 4. d5 d6 5. Nc3 exd5 6. cxd5 g6 7. Bf4 a6 8. a4 ({Here White has the interesting option} 8. e4 b5 9. e5 $6 (9. Qe2 Be7 $1 {After White has allowed the queenside expansion and blocked his kingside development, Black can make this concession to parry the threats on the e-file. It is better to immediately correct the queen's position with} 10. Qc2 {, but after} ({Now} 10. e5 $2 {backfires after} dxe5 11. Bxe5 (11. Nxe5 O-O 12. O-O-O Bd6) 11... Nbd7 $15) 10... O-O 11. Be2 Re8 12. O-O Bf8 {Black has nothing to complain about.}) 9... dxe5 10. Nxe5 Bd6 {is already slightly better for Black.}) 8... Bg7 9. h3 Qe7 10. e3 Nbd7 11. Be2 ({Also possible is} 11. Nd2 Ne5 12. Nc4 (12. Bxe5 {does not achieve anything after} Qxe5 13. Nc4 Qe7 14. Nb6 Rb8 15. a5 O-O 16. Be2 Nd7 17. Nxc8 Rfxc8 18. O-O Re8) 12... Nxc4 13. Bxc4 O-O 14. O-O Nd7 15. e4 Ne5 16. Be2 {, and now Black has several options: The immediate} f5 {is probably best, for example} (16... g5 $5) (16... Bd7 17. Be3 g5 ({or} 17... f5)) 17. exf5 Bxf5 18. Bg3 Rae8 $15) 11... O-O 12. O-O Ne8 13. Qc2 (13. Nd2 Ne5 {is also satisfactory for Black, for example} 14. Bg3 f5 15. f4 (15. Qc2 b6 $5 {Slowly preparing b6-b5 without allowing White to fix the queenside.}) 15... Nd3 $1) 13... Rb8 (13... Ne5 $6 {leads to favourable trades for White here:} 14. Nxe5 Bxe5 15. Bxe5 Qxe5 (15... dxe5 $2 16. a5 $16) 16. e4 $14) 14. Nd2 Ne5 $1 {Now this move is justified, anticipating White's idea of Nc4.} 15. Bg3 f5 16. f4 Nf7 17. Bf2 Nc7 18. Bf3 ({After} 18. a5 {, Black can make good use of the b5-square:} Bd7 19. Nc4 Nb5 ({or} 19... Bb5)) 18... b5 19. axb5 axb5 20. Rfe1 Qd8 21. Rab1 Bb7 {Black is in no hurry to cede control of the c4-square.} (21... b4 22. Nd1 Bd7 23. Nc4 $13) 22. b4 cxb4 $1 $15 23. Rxb4 Rc8 24. Rb3 $2 Nxd5 $17 25. Ndb1 b4 26. Bxd5 Bxd5 27. Rxb4 Qc7 28. Rc1 Be4 29. Rxe4 fxe4 30. Qxe4 Qc4 31. Qxc4 Rxc4 32. Ne2 Rxc1+ 33. Nxc1 Rb8 34. Nd2 Rb2 35. Nf1 Rb1 36. Ne2 d5 37. g4 Nd6 38. Neg3 Nc4 39. Kg2 Rb2 40. Kf3 Rb3 41. Ke2 Bf8 42. h4 Bd6 43. h5 Kf7 44. hxg6+ hxg6 45. Be1 Ra3 46. Bf2 d4 47. exd4 Bxf4 48. Ne4 Ke6 49. Nfg3 Bxg3 50. Nxg3 Kd5 51. Kf1 Ne3+ 52. Bxe3 Rxe3 53. Ne2 Ke4 54. Kf2 Rd3 55. d5 Ke5 56. d6 Rxd6 57. Ke3 Ra6 58. Kf3 Ra3+ 59. Kg2 Ra2 60. Kf3 Rxe2 61. Kxe2 Kf4 62. g5 Kxg5 63. Kf3 Kh4 64. Kg2 Kg4 65. Kg1 Kg3 0-1

