1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. g3 c5 4. d5 exd5 5. cxd5 d6 6. Nc3 g6 7. Bg2 Bg7 8. Nf3 O-O 9. O-O a6 10. a4 Nbd7 11. Nd2 Re8 12. h3 Nh5 13. Kh2 $6 {After this somewhat passive move Black has the initiative.} f5 ({It was also possible to play on the queenside:} 13... Rb8 14. a5 ({Or} 14. Nc4 Ne5) 14... b5 15. axb6 Nxb6 {, and now} 16. Nb3 {doesn't work:} Nc4 17. Ra4 Rb4 $15) 14. Nc4 ({An interesting attempt to exploit the weakening of the e6-square is} 14. Nf3 $5 Ne5 15. Ng5 $13) 14... Ne5 15. Nxe5 (15. Na3 f4 $40) 15... Bxe5 16. e3 Rb8 (16... Bd7 {may have been slightly preferable, connecting the heavy pieces while also preparing b7-b5.}) 17. Qd3 ({Also possible was} 17. a5 b5 18. axb6 Rxb6 ({or} 18... Qxb6)) 17... Bd7 18. a5 Qh4 $1 19. Kg1 (19. Ne2 {loses to} Bb5 20. Qc2 Bxe2 21. Qxe2 Nxg3 22. fxg3 Qxg3+ 23. Kg1 Qh2+ 24. Kf2 Bg3+ 25. Kf3 Bh4 $19) 19... Nxg3 20. fxg3 Qxg3 21. Rf3 Qh2+ 22. Kf2 f4 {Black had a strong attack and was already winning after the following mistake.} (22... Bf6 $5) 23. exf4 $2 Bd4+ $19 24. Be3 Rxe3 25. Rxe3 Re8 26. Qxd4 ({Or} 26. Rae1 Qxf4+ 27. Bf3 Qh2+ 28. Bg2 Bxh3) 26... cxd4 27. Rxe8+ Bxe8 28. Ne2 d3 29. Ng3 Bd7 30. Rh1 d2 31. Rxh2 d1=Q 32. Ne4 Qd4+ 33. Kg3 h5 34. Bf3 Bf5 35. Re2 Qg1+ 36. Bg2 h4+ 0-1

