1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 e6 4. Nc3 exd5 5. cxd5 d6 6. Nf3 g6 7. Bf4 Bg7 8. Nd2 O-O 9. Nc4 Nh5 10. Qd2 $2 {A terrible mistake. White's dark-squared bishop is his most important piece. For the remaining game he will have a hard time defending this colour complex.} ({After all the previous moves, White had to go for the complicated} 10. Bxd6 Re8 {, which offers Black a dangerous lead in development and the initiative, but at least White has a pawn for the suffering, and his important bishop is still alive!}) 10... Nxf4 11. Qxf4 Nd7 12. e3 (12. Nxd6 Be5) (12. Qxd6 b5 13. Nxb5 Rb8) 12... Ne5 13. Rc1 (13. Nxe5 Bxe5 14. Qa4 a6 (14... f5) 15. Qc2 b5 16. a3 f5 (16... Bd7)) 13... f5 14. h4 a6 15. Be2 b5 16. Nxe5 Bxe5 17. Qg5 Bf6 18. Qf4 Be5 19. Qg5 Bf6 20. Qf4 Ra7 21. g3 Re7 22. Bf3 Be5 23. Qg5 Kg7 24. e4 f4 25. h5 Bf6 26. h6+ Kg8 0-1

