1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nf3 Bg7 4. g3 O-O 5. Bg2 c5 6. d5 e6 7. Nc3 exd5 8. cxd5 d6 9. O-O a6 10. a4 Nbd7 11. Nd2 Nh5 {As usual, preparing to oust the white knight from c4 immediately.} ({Also possible was} 11... Re8 12. Nc4 Ne5 ({or} 12... Nb6) {, and for example} 13. Nxe5 Rxe5 14. Bf4 Re8 15. Re1 Rb8 (15... Ng4 16. Qc2 Ne5 17. Bxe5 Bxe5 18. e4 Bd7 19. f4 Bd4+ 20. Kh1 b5 (20... f5)) 16. a5 b5 17. axb6 Rxb6 18. Qc2 Rb4) ({Black needs to be careful, as} 11... Rb8 $2 {runs into a tactical refutation after} 12. Nc4 Nb6 $4 13. Nxd6 $18) 12. Nc4 Ne5 13. Na3 f5 (13... Bd7 $5) 14. e3 {Preventing f5-f4 but weakening the light squares while not achieving anything actively.} ({White hardly has the time for} 14. h3 f4 15. g4 Qh4 $1 {, and after} 16. gxh5 Bxh3 {, Black's attack is devastating.}) 14... Bd7 ({Even stronger was} 14... b5 15. axb5 axb5 16. Ncxb5 Ba6 $17) 15. Rb1 Qc7 16. Bd2 Nf6 17. Qe2 Be8 18. f4 Ned7 19. b4 cxb4 20. Rxb4 Nc5 21. Rfb1 Bf7 22. Nc2 Nfe4 23. Nxe4 Nxe4 24. Rxe4 fxe4 25. Bxe4 Rfe8 26. Qd3 b5 27. axb5 axb5 28. Rxb5 Ra2 29. Qb3 Rb2 0-1

