{This game is another example of premature play on the flank being punished with an energetical central breakthrough.} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 e6 4. Nc3 exd5 5. cxd5 d6 6. e4 g6 7. h3 Bg7 8. Bd3 O-O 9. Nf3 a6 10. a4 Nbd7 11. O-O Nh5 12. Bg5 Bf6 13. Be3 Rb8 14. Re1 Ne5 15. Be2 Nxf3+ 16. Bxf3 Ng7 17. Bf4 b5 $2 (17... Re8 18. Qd3 $14) 18. e5 ({Even better was} 18. axb5 axb5 19. e5 dxe5 20. Rxe5 $16 (20. Bxe5 $2 {is much worse:} Bxe5 21. Rxe5 b4 {Can the knight move towards the centre or does he have to move backwards? As usual, the success of Black's queenside expansion depends on this question.} 22. Ne4 $2 f6 $17) 20... Bxe5 21. Bxe5 Rb6 22. Ne4 ({Or} 22. Ra7)) 18... Bxe5 19. Rxe5 dxe5 20. Bxe5 Rb6 21. d6 $16 {Even without the open a-file, White has clearly more than enough compensation for the exchange.} Re8 22. Qd5 $2 (22. a5 $1 Rb7 23. Bh2 $1) 22... Bb7 $132 23. Qxc5 Ne6 24. Qe3 Bxf3 25. Qxf3 Rxd6 $2 26. Ne4 $2 (26. Bxd6 Qxd6 27. Ne4 $18) 26... Nd4 27. Nf6+ Rxf6 28. Qxf6 Qxf6 29. Bxf6 Nc2 30. Rc1 Re1+ $11 31. Rxe1 Nxe1 32. axb5 axb5 33. Kf1 Nd3 34. Ke2 Nf4+ 35. Kf3 Nd5 36. Bd4 f5 37. Ke2 Kf7 38. Be5 Ke6 39. Bb8 Nb4 40. Kd2 Kd5 41. Kc3 Nc6 42. Bc7 Ke4 43. Bd6 f4 44. h4 f3 45. g4 h5 46. gxh5 gxh5 47. Bg3 Nd4 48. Kb4 Nf5 49. Bc7 Nxh4 50. Kxb5 Nf5 51. Kc5 Kd3 52. Kd5 Nd4 53. b4 Nb5 54. Bg3 Ke2 55. Kc5 Na3 56. b5 Nxb5 57. Kxb5 Kf1 58. Kc4 Kg2 59. Kd3 Kh3 60. Ke3 h4 61. Kxf3 hxg3 62. fxg3 Kh2 63. g4 Kg1 64. g5 Kh2 65. g6 Kg1 66. g7 Kf1 67. g8=Q Ke1 68. Qd5 Kf1 69. Qd1# 1-0

