1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 c5 4. d5 exd5 5. cxd5 d6 6. Nc3 g6 7. Nd2 Bg7 (7... Nbd7 {is better suited to restrict White's possibilities, as now} 8. Nc4 {can be met with} Nb6) 8. e4 (8. Nc4 $144 O-O 9. Bf4) 8... O-O 9. Be2 Re8 10. O-O Nbd7 11. h3 a6 ({Another thematic move is} 11... g5 {, securing the e5-square and preparing further play on the kingside. and} 12. Nc4 ({Possible continuations are} 12. a4 Ne5 13. Re1 a6 14. Nc4 Nxc4 15. Bxc4 Nd7 ({Or} 15... g4 16. h4 g3 $5) 16. Bd2 Ne5 17. Bf1 g4 18. hxg4 Bxg4 19. f3 Qh4 {, with attacking chances on the kingside,}) 12... Nxe4 13. Nxe4 Rxe4 14. Nxd6 Rd4 $13) 12. a4 Rb8 {Black will hardly be able to force b7-b5, but this way she adds further dynamics to the position and ties two minor pieces to the defense of the b5-square. Which White was not happy about, as his next move shows.} ({Also possible was the immediate} 12... g5 {, for example} 13. Re1 Ne5 14. Nf3 ({or} 14. Nf1 h6 15. Ng3 Bd7 16. a5 Qc7 17. Bd2 Ng6 18. Bf1 Nh4 19. Ra3 Re7 20. Qc2 Rae8) 14... Nxf3+ 15. Bxf3 Nd7 16. Bg4 Ne5 17. Bxc8 Rxc8 18. f4 gxf4 19. Bxf4 c4 20. Bxe5 Bxe5 {, with a good position.}) 13. a5 {A slightly surprising decision by White. This move is usually only played when b7-b5 is threatened and hard or impossible to prevent by other means.} ({A very thematic move is} 13. Ra3 {Later the rook can perform defensive as well as offensive tasks on the kingside.}) 13... b5 $6 {This may be slightly premature.} ({Probably better was} 13... g5 14. Qc2 Ne5 {, starting the usual play on the kingside while keeping the option to open the queenside at a more favourable moment.}) 14. axb6 Nxb6 15. Bd3 ({Of course,} 15. Bxa6 Ra8 {is not what White wants.}) 15... g5 $2 {And this is too much, creating weaknesses on both flanks while lacking adequate counterplay, with both knights being two moves away from the desired e5-square.} 16. f4 $1 gxf4 17. Rxf4 Nbd7 18. Nc4 Ne5 19. Nxe5 Rxe5 20. Rf3 Nd7 21. Rg3 Nf8 22. Bxa6 Ng6 (22... Ra8 {can now be answered with} 23. Bh6) 23. Bxc8 Qxc8 24. Ra7 Rb7 25. Rxb7 Qxb7 26. Rf3 Re8 27. Rf1 Ne5 28. Qh5 Ng6 29. Qf5 Re5 30. Qf3 h6 31. Ne2 Qd7 32. Ng3 Nh4 33. Qd3 Qb7 34. Qe2 Qd7 35. Bf4 Re8 36. Qh5 Ng6 37. Bxh6 Bxb2 38. Bg5 Bd4+ 39. Kh1 Qb5 40. Rxf7 Kxf7 41. Qh7+ Bg7 42. Nf5 Qf1+ 43. Kh2 1-0

