1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 c5 4. d5 exd5 5. cxd5 d6 6. Nc3 g6 7. e4 Bg7 (7... a6 {is more precise, and Black will be able to play either Bg4 or b7-b5.}) 8. h3 O-O 9. Bd3 b5 10. a3 $5 {An unusual choice. Now the game transposes to the 7... a6 8.h3 b5 line.} ({The critical moves are of course} 10. Bxb5) ({and} 10. Nxb5) 10... a6 11. O-O Nbd7 12. Bg5 $6 {Not the best square for the bishop. The queen will soon leave the pin and move to b6 anyway.} (12. Bf4 $142 Qb6 13. Re1 Nh5 14. Bh2 c4 15. Bc2 Bb7) 12... Re8 13. Re1 Bb7 14. Qd2 Qb6 $6 (14... c4 $1) 15. Nh2 $2 {This decentralising move does not have many merits.} (15. b4 $1 {was correct, taking control of the c5-square.} Rac8 16. Rac1 Nh5 {, with chances for both sides, for example} 17. g4 Nhf6 18. Bf4 h5 19. g5 Nh7 $13) 15... Rac8 16. Bc2 a5 $36 17. Nf3 (17. a4 b4 18. Nb5 Ba6 $17) 17... b4 18. Na4 Qc7 19. Rac1 Ba6 20. Bf4 Bb5 21. axb4 axb4 22. Ra1 Ra8 23. e5 {A desperate attempt to get active play.} (23. b3 {does not work for several reasons, the most devastating being} Nxe4 24. Bxe4 Bxa1 25. Rxa1 Rxe4 $19) 23... dxe5 24. Be3 Ra6 25. Rec1 e4 26. Ne1 Rea8 27. b3 Qd6 28. Rab1 c4 0-1

