1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 e6 4. Nc3 exd5 5. cxd5 d6 6. Nf3 g6 7. Nd2 Nbd7 8. e4 (8. Nc4 {can be met with} Nb6) 8... Bg7 9. Be2 O-O 10. O-O {This is the initial position of the variation with Nd2 and e2-e4. White would like to establish a strong position in the centre with Nc4 and Bf4 or f2-f4, but for the moment, his pieces are not so well coordinated and the bishop on c1 is blocked. It is important for Black to prevent this kind of ideal white setup and always be able to dislodge the knight from c4.} Re8 11. a4 ({White has many moves here:} 11. Re1 a6 12. a4 g5 $5 13. Qc2 Ne5 $132 14. Nf1 h6 15. Ng3 Bd7 16. a5 Ng6 17. Bd2 Nf4) (11. Qc2) (11. h3 {To meet Ne5 with f2-f4.} g5 $5 $132 {Securing the e5-square for the knight.} 12. Nc4 Nxe4 13. Nxe4 Rxe4 14. Nxd6 Rd4 15. Qc2 Nb6 16. Nxc8 Rxc8 $132) (11. Qc2 Ne5 $1 12. a4 a6 (12... Bg4 $5 13. f3 Bd7 $132) 13. b3 g5 14. Bb2 b6 $132) 11... a6 (11... Ne5 $5 12. f4 $2 (12. Ra3 {A standard move in these positions. On the third rank, the rook can be used both as an attacker and defender.} a6 $144 (12... g5 13. Nf3 (13. Bb5 Re7 (13... Bd7 $2 {would be a strategical blunder. In positions with a pawn on g5, the bishop needs to guard the f5-square against a knight that might invade for example via f1-g3.}) 14. Re1 a6 15. Bf1 h6 16. Qc2 Bd7 17. a5 Qc7 18. Nd1 Rae8 $132) 13... Nxf3+ 14. Bxf3 Nd7 $132 ({or} 14... h6))) (12. h3 g5 {As usual after h2-h3, Black should prevent f2-f4.} 13. Nf3 Nxf3+ 14. Bxf3 h6 $132) 12... Neg4 13. Nc4 Nxe4 14. Bxg4 Bd4+ 15. Kh1 Bxg4 16. Qxg4 Nf2+ 17. Rxf2 Re1+) (11... g5 $144 {transposes to lines above.}) 12. Qc2 (12. f3 $6 Ne5 13. Qc2 Nh5 $36 {Black has several active ideas like Nf4, Qh4 and f7-f5. For example} 14. Nc4 Nxc4 15. Bxc4 Bd4+ ({or the less forcing} 15... Be5 $5) 16. Kh1 Qh4 17. Ne2 Be5 $15) 12... Rb8 (12... Ne5 $1 {may have been better:} 13. h3 (13. f4 $2 Neg4 14. Nc4 Nxe4 15. Nxe4 Bd4+ 16. Kh1 Nxh2 $1) (13. a5 g5 14. Ra3 Bd7) 13... g5 14. Nc4 (14. Nf3 Nxf3+ 15. Bxf3 h6) 14... Nxc4 15. Bxc4 g4 $1 ({After} 15... h6 16. f4 gxf4 17. Bxf4 {, White may be slightly preferable.}) 16. hxg4 (16. h4 Nh5 17. g3 Qf6 $132 ({Or} 17... Nf6)) 16... Nxg4 $36 17. Bf4 Qh4 18. Bxd6 $2 Re5 $1 $19) 13. Rb1 Ne5 14. b4 cxb4 15. Rxb4 Nh5 16. Nc4 Nxc4 17. Rxc4 Bd7 18. Bxh5 gxh5 19. Ne2 b5 20. axb5 Bxb5 21. Ng3 Rc8 22. Rxc8 Qxc8 23. Qxc8 Rxc8 24. Re1 Bc3 25. Nf5 Rc7 26. Re3 Be5 27. Ba3 Bd7 28. g4 Bxf5 29. gxf5 Rc2 30. f6 h6 31. Rb3 Ra2 32. Bb4 Rc2 33. Kg2 Kh7 34. Kf3 Rc4 35. Bd2 Kg6 36. h3 Ra4 37. Bf4 Kxf6 38. Bxh6 Kg6 39. Be3 f5 40. exf5+ Kxf5 41. Rb8 a5 42. Rf8+ Kg6 43. Rg8+ Kf6 44. Rf8+ Kg6 45. Rg8+ Kf7 46. Rg5 h4 47. Rg1 Rc4 48. Rb1 a4 49. Rb7+ Kg6 50. Ra7 Kf5 51. Rf7+ Bf6 52. Ra7 Bb2 53. Rf7+ Ke5 54. Ra7 Kxd5 55. Ke2 a3 56. Kd3 Rc3+ 57. Kd2 Rc8 58. Kd3 Rc3+ 59. Kd2 Rc1 60. Ra5+ Ke6 61. Ra4 Rh1 62. Kc2 Rxh3 0-1

