{[%evp 0,76,13,29,18,-8,33,43,61,66,71,62,109,109,125,80,83,57,57,37,5,7,40,41,25,30,40,23,16,18,21,35,41,9,46,4,-7,-16,-17,-3,-3,-17,-6,-16,-14,-2,-10,-11,-5,-14,-13,-12,-18,-39,-20,-43,-60,-88,-88,-61,2,-25,-67,-110,-110,-183,-221,-305,-320,-452,-545,-602,-709,-709,-410,-1003,-1221,-29997,-29998] the small theory of the 7.Bg5 line} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 e6 (3... e5 4. Nc3 d6 5. e4 Be7) 4. Nc3 exd5 5. cxd5 g6 6. Nf3 d6 7. Bg5 Bg7 (7... h6 $1 8. Bh4 g5 9. Bg3 Nh5 10. e3 (10. e4) 10... Nxg3 11. hxg3 Bg7 12. Bb5+ (12. Nd2 O-O $1 13. Bd3 f5 14. a4 Na6 (14... Nd7 15. Nc4 Ne5 $2 (15... Nb6 16. a5 Nxc4 17. Bxc4 Bd7 18. O-O a6 19. Na4 Qf6 20. Nb6 Rad8 21. Rb1 Be8) 16. Nxe5 Bxe5 (16... dxe5 17. e4 f4 18. Bc4 (18. d6)) 17. Rxh6)) 12... Nd7 (12... Kf8)) 8. e3 a6 9. a4 h6 10. Bf4 $2 {a terrible move because now to take the bishop, we don't have to weaken our light squares with g5, so we can go Nh5!} (10. Bh4 {and we will get into our positions} g5 11. Bg3 Nh5 12. Nd2 Nxg3 13. hxg3 Nd7 (13... f5 {is too early, Black can play f5 when it's not a blunder and when the pieces can be developed, such as f5 there might be Qh5+, so that means 0-0. Another reason not f5 is because of Nc4, and we can't meet it with Ne5 or Nb6, so it is much better to go Nd7 first}) (13... O-O 14. Be2 Nd7 (14... f5 15. Nc4 {the same reason as above, Nc4 can't be met with Ne5 or Nb6}) 15. O-O f5) 14. Nc4 Ne5 15. Be2 Nxc4 16. Bxc4 O-O {[%cal Gf7f5]} 17. O-O (17. Qh5 f5 18. O-O-O Bd7 $19 {White doesn't have any attack and b5 might be coming soon}) 17... Bd7 (17... f5) 18. Qc2 f5 $17) 10... g5 $6 (10... Nh5 $1 11. Bg3 Nxg3 12. hxg3 O-O {White doesn't have any attack, we are pretty safe with the Bg7} 13. Be2 (13. Nd2 Nd7 14. Nc4 Nb6 (14... Qe7 15. Be2 Ne5 16. Nxe5 (16. Nb6 Rb8 17. Nxc8 Rbxc8 18. O-O f5 19. e4) 16... Qxe5 17. O-O Bd7 18. e4 f5 19. f4 Qd4+ 20. Qxd4 cxd4 21. Na2 fxe4) 15. Be2 Nxc4 16. Bxc4 Bd7 17. O-O h5) (13. Qc2 {with the idea of going 0-0-0 is a bad idea, Black can always consider b5 after 0-0-0 to open up the queenside and attack the White king} Nd7 14. O-O-O b5 $19) 13... Nd7 14. O-O Re8 (14... Rb8) (14... Ne5) (14... Qe7) (14... f5)) (10... Bg4 11. Be2 Bxf3 12. Bxf3) 11. Bg3 Nh5 12. Nd2 Nxg3 13. hxg3 Nd7 14. Be2 (14. Nc4 Ne5 15. Be2 O-O $2 (15... Nxc4 16. Bxc4 O-O 17. O-O Bd7 18. Qc2 f5) 16. Nxe5) 14... Rb8 (14... O-O) (14... Qe7) 15. Qb3 Qc7 (15... Nf6 16. Bxa6) 16. Qc2 Nf6 17. Rb1 Bd7 18. e4 b5 19. axb5 axb5 20. Nd1 Ng4 (20... O-O) 21. Bxg4 Bxg4 22. Ne3 Bd7 23. g4 Qa7 24. Nf5 Bxf5 25. gxf5 c4 26. O-O g4 27. Ra1 Qd4 28. Ra6 Be5 29. Kh1 Bf4 (29... Qxb2 30. Qxb2 Bxb2 31. Rxd6 O-O) 30. Nb1 Qf6 31. g3 Be5 32. Nc3 h5 33. Nxb5 h4 34. Nxd6+ (34. Nc7+ Kf8) (34. Kg2 hxg3 35. fxg3 Qh6 (35... Rh2+ 36. Kxh2 Qh4+ 37. Kg1 Qxg3+ 38. Qg2 Qxg2+ 39. Kxg2 Rxb5)) 34... Bxd6 35. Qxc4 hxg3+ 36. Kg1 Rd8 (36... Rh1+ 37. Kg2 Rh2+ 38. Kg1 gxf2+ 39. Rxf2 Rxf2 40. Kxf2 Rxb2+ 41. Kf1 Rb1+ 42. Ke2 Qb2+ 43. Ke3 Re1+ 44. Kd3 Qe2+ 45. Kd4 Be5+ (45... Qxe4+ 46. Kc3 Rc1+) 46. Kc5 Qxc4+ 47. Kxc4 Rc1+ 48. Kb5 g3) 37. fxg3 Qh6 38. Qc2 Bc5+ 0-1

