1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 c5 4. d5 exd5 5. cxd5 d6 6. Nc3 g6 7. Bf4 a6 8. a4 Bg7 9. h3 (9. Nd2 {the idea is Nc4 but this move allows} Nh5 {removing the pressure from the d6 pawn} 10. Be3 Nd7 {typical way to fight against Nc4} (10... f5 {[%cal Gf5f4]}) 11. Nc4 Ne5 12. Nxe5 Bxe5 {when there is a knight on h5 we can either combine it with f5-f4 or we should go back at some point}) 9... O-O 10. e3 Ne8 {protecting d6 and preparing to go Nd7} 11. Be2 (11. Nd2 {White can spend some time and try to put pressure on d6, but we can meet that with Ne5} Nd7 12. Nc4 Ne5 {very unique idea in the Benoni, but here it works} 13. Nxe5 (13. Bxe5 Bxe5 (13... dxe5 {not dxe5 because we close our bishop and White may have d6} 14. d6) 14. Nxe5 dxe5 15. Be2 Nd6 16. a5 Bd7 17. Na4 Bxa4 18. Rxa4 f5 {[%csl Gd6] the knight on d6 are very good}) 13... dxe5 14. Bh2 Nd6 {b6 was also playable} 15. a5 Bd7) 11... Nd7 12. O-O Rb8 (12... Ne5 {is again possible} 13. Qc2 Nxf3+ 14. Bxf3 f5 15. Bh2 Bd7 16. Qd2 g5 17. a5 Qe7 (17... Nc7 18. Bxd6) 18. Na4 Bxa4 19. Rxa4 Nc7 20. b4 cxb4 21. Rxb4 Nb5) 13. Nd2 {Black again has several moves to choose from} (13. a5 {might be more accurate for White}) 13... Qe7 (13... Ne5 14. Bg3 f5 {with perhaps Nc7 next}) (13... b6 14. Nc4 (14. Re1 Ne5 15. Bg3 f5 16. Qc2 Nc7 (16... Nf7) 17. Nf3 Nxf3+ 18. Bxf3 b5) 14... Ne5 15. Bxe5 Bxe5 16. Nxe5 dxe5) 14. Qc2 b6 15. Rab1 Nc7 (15... Ne5 {is a better move than Nc7, not allowing the knight to go to c4} 16. Nc4 Nxc4 17. Bxc4 f5 {f5 taking some space, controlling e4, and next can be either Nc7 preparing b5 or g5} (17... Nc7 18. Ne4 {on Nc7 Ne4 needs to be calculated}) (17... g5 {is also possible} 18. Bh2 f5) 18. e4 $2 g5 $1 19. Bd2 f4 {with a much better position for Black} 20. f3 Be5) 16. Rfd1 (16. Nc4 {seems like a more logical move} Ne5 17. Bxe5 Bxe5 18. Nxe5 Qxe5 {[%cal Gb6b5] with a comfortable position}) 16... Ne5 17. b4 Bf5 18. e4 Bd7 19. bxc5 bxc5 20. Bg3 g5 21. Nc4 Nxc4 22. Bxc4 Be5 23. Bxe5 Qxe5 24. Ne2 a5 25. Rxb8 Rxb8 26. Rb1 Rb4 27. Rxb4 cxb4 28. Bb3 Na6 29. Ng3 Nc5 30. Qc4 Qc3 31. Qxc3 bxc3 32. Ne2 Nxb3 0-1

