{an important game for the typical plans of the Bf4-e3 variation !! ...study it carefully!} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 c5 4. d5 d6 5. Nc3 exd5 6. cxd5 (6. Nxd5 Nxd5 7. cxd5 Be7) 6... g6 7. Bf4 a6 $1 8. a4 (8. Nd2 Nbd7 $1 $132 9. e4 (9. Nc4 Nb6 $1 $36) 9... b5) 8... Bg7 9. h3 (9. e3 Bg4 {Bg4 again and it would resemble positions with e4} 10. Be2 Bxf3 11. Bxf3 O-O 12. O-O Qe7 13. Qb3 {this is a bit annoying since it puts pressure on b7 and doesn't allow Nbd7, so here we can simply go Qc7 and then Nbd7} (13. h3 Nbd7) 13... Qc7 $1 (13... Nbd7 14. Qxb7 {the queen is not trapped, the c6 square is available and there will be pressure on d6}) 14. h3 Nbd7) 9... O-O 10. e3 Ne8 $5 {the simplest} 11. Be2 (11. a5 {a5 is possible at any moment, but it might be a bit premature, in any case, Black can go Nd7 Rb8 and b5}) 11... Nd7 (11... b6 $5 {is also interesting} 12. Nd2 (12. O-O Nd7 {'!' 'Tiger Hillarp Persson game'} 13. Nd2 (13. e4 Rb8 (13... Qe7 $132)) 13... Ne5 14. e4 (14. Bh2 {white can perhaps go f4, so we just go f5} f5 15. Qb3 Rb8 16. Kh1 Nc7 17. f4 Nf7 18. Bf3 b5 19. axb5 axb5 20. Rfe1) 14... g5 (14... f5 $1 $132 15. exf5 Bxf5 16. Bg3 (16. Nde4 $4 Bxe4 17. Nxe4 Rxf4) 16... Nc7 $1 17. Nde4 Rb8 $15 18. Qd2 b5 (18... Re8) 19. axb5 axb5)) 12... Nd7 13. Nc4 $6 (13. O-O Ne5 14. Bg3 f5) 13... Ne5 14. Nxe5 $6 (14. Bxe5 $5 Bxe5 $1 15. Qb3 (15. Nxe5 dxe5 16. O-O Nd6 $15) 15... Rb8 16. Na5 Qg5 $36 17. Bf3 Nf6 18. Nc6 Rb7) 14... dxe5 15. Bh2 Nd6 $15 16. O-O f5 $17 17. Rc1 Ra7 $15 (17... Bd7 $5 $15 18. Qc2 b5 $15) 18. Nb1 f4 (18... Rd7 19. a5 b5 20. Rxc5 Nb7 21. Rc1 Rxd5) 19. a5) 12. O-O (12. a5 Ne5 13. Nd2 (13. Nxe5 $6 dxe5 14. Bh2 Nd6 15. O-O Bd7 16. Qd2 f5 17. Na4 Bxa4 18. Rxa4 Rc8 $132) 13... Bf5 14. O-O (14. e4 Bd7) 14... Nd3) 12... Ne5 $5 13. Nxe5 (13. Nd2 f5 $132 (13... Bd7 14. Bg3 f5) (13... Bf5) (13... b6 $132) (13... Rb8 14. Bh2 (14. Nc4 Nxc4 15. Bxc4 Nc7) 14... f5 15. Qc2 Bd7 16. a5 Qe7 (16... Nc7 $1 $132) 17. Rae1 g5 $6 (17... Nc7 $1 $132 18. f4 Nf7 19. e4 fxe4 20. Ndxe4 (20. Ncxe4 Nxd5 $17) 20... b5 21. axb6 Rxb6 22. Bc4 Qd8 $132 23. b3 Nb5) 18. f4 {1-0 (37) Donchenko, A-Villwock,M/Maastricht NED 2018})) (13. a5 Nxf3+ 14. Bxf3 Rb8 (14... g5 $1 15. Bh2 f5 $132) (14... f5 15. Qd2 {White may threaten to go e4, but Black can go g5! first} g5 16. Bh2 {so now whenever White goes e4, Black can answer with f4!} Bd7 17. Be2 Qe7 {black is doing very well, and now if White goes} 18. f4 {we can either keep the tension with h6 or we can go g4} g4 (18... h6) 19. hxg4 fxg4 20. e4 Qh4 {[%cal Gg4g3]} 21. g3 {[%csl Rf4,Rg3,Rh2]}) 15. Qd2 b5 16. axb6 Rxb6 17. Ra2 Nc7 $132) (13. Bxe5 $5 dxe5 14. a5 Nd6 15. Nd2 f5 16. Nc4 (16. Na4 Qxa5) (16. Nb3 c4) 16... Nxc4 17. Bxc4 Qd6 18. Ra3 Bf6 $1 19. e4 (19. Rb3 Bd8) 19... Bd7 (19... Bd8 20. Qd2 Bd7 21. Rb3 Rb8) 20. Rb3 (20. Re1 Rae8) 20... Bd8 21. Rxb7) 13... dxe5 14. Bh2 (14. Bg3 Nd6 15. a5 Bd7 (15... Bf5) 16. Qd2 (16. Na4 Qxa5) 16... f5 $15 17. Na4 Ne4) 14... Nd6 {Black is doing very well} 15. a5 (15. e4 {can be met with} f5 16. f4 (16. exf5 Bxf5 $132 (16... gxf5 $1 $132)) 16... exf4 $17) 15... Bd7 $132 16. Na4 Qxa5 0-1

