{very nice typical play ...in the Bf4-e3-h3 line....study many games like that. ..to get a nce feeling of the positions!} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 c5 4. d5 d6 5. Nc3 exd5 6. cxd5 g6 7. Bf4 a6 8. a4 (8. e4 b5 9. e5 (9. Qe2 Be7 $3 10. Qc2 O-O 11. Be2 Re8 12. O-O Bf8) 9... dxe5 10. Nxe5 Bd6) 8... Bg7 9. h3 Qe7 {is a bit premature since we are going 0-0 and Ne8, not Qe7 immediately} 10. e3 Nbd7 11. Be2 ({if} 11. Nd2 {we can jump in} Ne5 12. Nc4 (12. Bxe5 Qxe5 13. Nc4 Qe7 14. Nb6 Rb8 15. Nxc8 Rxc8 {this Nb6 Nxc8 is hardly ever a problem in the benoni} 16. Be2 O-O 17. Qc2 Nd7 (17... Rfe8 {with Ne4 as an idea, or Nd7 f5 but in this case it might be better with the rook on f8}) 18. O-O f5 {is also a good idea}) 12... Nxc4 13. Bxc4 O-O 14. O-O {Black is thrilled to exchange one pair of minor pieces. Black can play Ne8 or Nh5 Bh2 f5, or even Nd7 now} Nd7 {the knight comes to e5 with tempo} (14... Nh5 15. Bh2 f5) 15. Qc2 (15. e4 Ne5 16. Be2 f5 $15 (16... g5) 17. exf5 Bxf5 18. Bg3 Rae8) 15... Ne5 16. Be2 Bd7 17. e4 (17. Bh2 {threatening f4 trapping our knight, so we go f5 to free the f7 square} f5 {Black has good play all over the board, regardless of a computer assessment, I consider this position as already better for Black}) 17... g5 (17... f5)) 11... O-O 12. O-O Ne8 13. Qc2 Rb8 {b6 was also possible} (13... Nc7 14. Ne4) (13... Ne5 $6 14. Nxe5 Bxe5 15. Bxe5 Qxe5 16. e4) 14. Nd2 Ne5 $1 15. Bg3 f5 16. f4 Nf7 17. Bf2 Nc7 {[%cal Gb7b5] intending b5} 18. Bf3 (18. a5 Bd7 19. Nc4 Nb5 (19... Bb5)) 18... b5 19. axb5 axb5 20. Rfe1 (20. Ra7 Qd8) 20... Qd8 {Black is doing very well} 21. Rab1 Bb7 (21... b4 22. Nd1 Bd7 23. Nc4) 22. b4 cxb4 $1 23. Rxb4 Rc8 24. Rb3 Nxd5 25. Ndb1 b4 26. Bxd5 Bxd5 27. Rxb4 Qc7 28. Rc1 Be4 29. Rxe4 fxe4 30. Qxe4 Qc4 31. Qxc4 Rxc4 32. Ne2 Rxc1+ 33. Nxc1 Rb8 34. Nd2 Rb2 35. Nf1 Rb1 36. Ne2 d5 37. g4 Nd6 38. Neg3 Nc4 39. Kg2 Rb2 40. Kf3 Rb3 41. Ke2 Bf8 42. h4 Bd6 43. h5 Kf7 44. hxg6+ hxg6 45. Be1 Ra3 46. Bf2 d4 47. exd4 Bxf4 48. Ne4 Ke6 49. Nfg3 Bxg3 50. Nxg3 Kd5 51. Kf1 Ne3+ 52. Bxe3 Rxe3 53. Ne2 Ke4 54. Kf2 Rd3 55. d5 Ke5 56. d6 Rxd6 57. Ke3 Ra6 58. Kf3 Ra3+ 59. Kg2 Ra2 60. Kf3 Rxe2 61. Kxe2 Kf4 62. g5 Kxg5 63. Kf3 Kh4 64. Kg2 Kg4 65. Kg1 Kg3 0-1

