1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 c5 4. d5 exd5 5. cxd5 d6 6. Nc3 g6 7. Bf4 a6 8. a4 Bg7 9. h3 O-O 10. e3 Ne8 11. Be2 (11. h4 {is a hazardous move} Nf6 {the situation is different now with h4, the g4 square is available. When the center is open, flank attacks often fail} (11... Bg4 12. Be2)) 11... Nd7 12. O-O Rb8 13. Nd2 (13. a5 Qe7 14. Nd2 Ne5 15. Bg3 f5 (15... b5 16. axb6 Rxb6 17. Bxe5 Bxe5 18. Nc4 Rb8 19. Qd2) 16. Qc2 Nc7 $132) 13... Ne5 14. a5 f5 {when top players are playing, the fight almost always includes typical moves and ideas} 15. Bg3 Bd7 {Nc7 was also possible, but Bd7 might be more accurate since it develops another piece} 16. Qb3 b5 (16... Nc7 17. Bxe5 Bxe5 18. Nc4 Qe7 19. Nxe5 Qxe5 20. Rac1 Ne8 (20... Na8 21. Qc2 b5 22. axb6 Rxb6 23. b3 Nc7 24. Bc4)) 17. axb6 Rxb6 18. Qc2 Bb5 {an interesting idea from Black} 19. Nxb5 axb5 {the computer may give some slight advantage to White but practically it doesn't mean anything, also c4 may be an idea for Black at some point} 20. Nb3 g5 21. Na5 f4 $15 22. Bh2 Nc7 {Black is doing very well} 23. Rfd1 Kh8 24. Qe4 Qf6 25. exf4 gxf4 26. Nb3 Na6 27. Nd2 c4 28. Qb1 Nc5 29. Ne4 Nxe4 30. Qxe4 Rb7 31. Ra5 Nd7 32. b4 cxb3 33. Bd3 Qh6 34. Qb4 Nc5 35. Bb1 Be5 36. Rxb5 Rg7 37. Be4 Nxe4 38. Qxe4 Qxh3 39. Kh1 Qh5 0-1

