1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 c5 4. d5 d6 5. Nc3 exd5 6. cxd5 g6 7. h3 $5 a6 $1 8. a4 Qe7 $1 9. Bf4 {here we can anticipate Nd2-Nc4 by starting with Nbd7, to meet it with Ne5} (9. g3 $5 {this will take us to a g3 Benoni, with all our typical ideas!}) 9... Bg7 (9... Nbd7 10. Nd2 Ne5 11. Bxe5 Qxe5 12. Nc4 Qe7 13. Nb6 Rb8 14. e3 Bg7 15. Be2 O-O 16. O-O Nd7 17. Nxc8 Rbxc8 {with a very nice game for Black}) 10. e3 (10. Nd2 {this can be a bit annoying, Nc4 is coming} Nbd7 11. Nc4 Ne5 12. Bxe5 dxe5 {and we are worse}) 10... O-O 11. Be2 Nbd7 12. O-O Ne8 (12... b6 $5 13. Qc2 Ne8 14. Rfe1 Ne5 $132) 13. a5 Rb8 14. Bh2 b5 15. axb6 Rxb6 16. Qc2 Ne5 17. Nd2 Nc7 18. Ra5 Rb4 19. b3 Bf5 20. e4 Bc8 21. Rd1 Rd4 22. Bf4 f5 23. Be3 f4 24. Bxd4 cxd4 25. Ncb1 d3 26. Bxd3 f3 27. Bf1 fxg2 28. Bxg2 Bxh3 29. Bxh3 Qh4 30. Nf1 Qxh3 31. Nh2 Bh6 32. Qc3 Nf3+ 33. Nxf3 Rxf3 34. Qxc7 Rg3+ 35. fxg3 Be3# 0-1

