1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 c5 4. d5 exd5 5. cxd5 d6 6. Nc3 g6 7. g3 Bg7 8. Bg2 O-O 9. O-O a6 10. a4 Re8 11. Bf4 Nh5 12. Bg5 Qc7 (12... Nf6 $144 13. e4 Bg4 14. h3 Bxf3 15. Bxf3 Nbd7) (12... f6 $2 13. Bd2 f5 14. Ng5 $16) 13. Rc1 h6 14. Bd2 Nd7 15. b3 (15. b4 {can be met with} Qd8 $1 16. bxc5 ({or} 16. b5 Ne5) 16... Nxc5 $15 {, for example} 17. Be3 Rxe3 18. fxe3 Nf6 ({or} 18... Bd7) 19. h3 Bd7 {, with very good positional compensation for the sacrificed exchange.}) 15... Rb8 (15... Ne5 $6 16. Nxe5 Rxe5 {Black would prefer to take back with the bishop, but the h6-pawn needs protection.} 17. e4 Re8 {Here White should be better, as Black has spent much time moving his rook and still needs to reroute the h5-knight.}) ({Also good is} 15... Nhf6 16. Bf4 Ng4 17. h3 Nge5 18. Nxe5 Nxe5 19. Qd2 Kh7 20. Rfe1 Bd7) 16. Re1 b5 17. axb5 axb5 18. e4 Nhf6 19. Qc2 Ba6 (19... b4 $1 20. Nd1 Ba6 $17 21. Nb2 Nxe4 22. Rxe4 Rxe4 23. Qxe4 Bxb2) 20. Nd1 {The remaining moves showed imprecisions and mistakes by both sides, with Black keeping the upper hand in the tactical complications.} Rec8 (20... b4 $1 $17) 21. Bf1 (21. Nd4 $1 {would have given White good counterchances.}) 21... Qb7 22. h3 Nb6 23. Bf4 Ne8 24. Qd2 Kh7 25. h4 b4 26. Bxa6 Qxa6 27. e5 c4 28. bxc4 Nxc4 29. Qe2 Ra8 30. Qe4 dxe5 31. Nxe5 Ned6 32. Qb1 Bxe5 33. Bxe5 Nd2 34. Rxc8 0-1

