1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 c5 4. d5 exd5 5. cxd5 d6 6. Nc3 g6 7. g3 Bg7 8. Bg2 O-O 9. O-O Re8 10. Bf4 Nh5 $1 {a great way to get out of book..and keep all the typical ideas of the benoni !} 11. Bg5 Qb6 $5 (11... f6 $2 12. Bd2 f5 13. Ng5 $18) (11... Nf6 $5) 12. Qd2 (12. e4 Bg4 $1 (12... Qxb2 13. Bd2 $3 $132) 13. Qd2 Bxf3 14. Bxf3 Nf6 15. Rfe1 Nbd7 16. Bg2 a6 17. a4 Qc7 18. Bh6 Bxh6 19. Qxh6 {This trade is usually a good idea for Black if the queen on h6 is unsupported and unable to create attacking chances. Black has a satisfactory Benoni position.}) (12. Nd2 $5 h6 $1 13. Be3 Nd7 $1 (13... Rxe3 {does not work here due to} 14. Nc4) 14. Nc4 (14. Rb1 Qd8 $1 $15 15. Nc4 Ne5 ({or} 15... Nb6 16. Nxb6 Qxb6)) 14... Qa6 15. Qb3 Ne5 16. Nxe5 Rxe5 17. Bd2 Bd7 $132) 12... Bg4 ({Also good are} 12... Nd7) ({and} 12... Nf6) 13. h3 Bxf3 14. Bxf3 Nf6 15. e4 Nbd7 16. Bg2 a6 17. Rac1 (17. a4 {can be well answered by either} Qa5 ({or} 17... Rab8)) 17... Qa5 18. Bf4 b5 19. Rfe1 (19. Bxd6 $2 b4 20. Nb1 Nxe4 21. Bxe4 Rxe4 22. Qd3 Rd4 23. Qf3 Qxa2 24. Bxc5 Qxd5 25. Qxd5 Rxd5 26. Bxb4 Bxb2 $17) 19... Qb6 20. b3 Rac8 21. g4 c4 22. b4 Ne5 23. Bxe5 Rxe5 24. Kh1 g5 25. f4 gxf4 26. Qxf4 Rce8 27. Rf1 R5e7 28. e5 dxe5 29. Qf5 e4 30. g5 Nh5 31. Qg4 Bxc3 32. Rxc3 Qg6 33. Re3 Re5 34. h4 f5 35. Qd1 f4 0-1

