1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. g3 c5 4. d5 exd5 5. cxd5 d6 6. Nc3 g6 7. Bg2 Bg7 8. Nf3 O-O 9. O-O Nbd7 ({As usual in the fianchetto line,} 9... Bg4 $2 {does not work due to} 10. Nd2) 10. a4 h6 $5 {A useful move in many lines that has the additional benefit of avoiding opening theory.} 11. Qc2 (11. Bf4 Qe7 12. Nb5 Ne8 {leads to nothing.}) 11... Qe7 12. Ra3 (12. Bf4 Ng4 13. h3 Nge5 14. Nd2 {, and Black has the pleasant choice between} f5 ({and} 14... g5 15. Be3 f5)) 12... a6 13. Nd2 Rb8 14. a5 ({After} 14. Re1 b5 15. axb5 axb5 16. Ra7 Qd8 17. e4 Qb6 18. Ra1 c4 19. b4 cxb3 {, Black has good counterplay.}) 14... b5 15. axb6 Nxb6 16. b3 ({It is important that} 16. Nb3 {, with the idea Nb3-a5-c6, can (and must) be met with} Nc4) 16... Ng4 17. Bb2 f5 18. e3 g5 19. Raa1 Bb7 20. Rae1 Rbe8 21. h3 Ne5 22. f4 Ng6 23. Kh2 gxf4 24. gxf4 Kh7 25. Nc4 Nxc4 26. bxc4 Bc8 27. Rf3 Rg8 28. Rg1 Bf6 29. Bh1 Ne5 30. Rfg3 Rxg3 31. Rxg3 Nxc4 32. Bc1 Bh4 33. Rf3 Qg7 34. Ne2 Nb6 35. e4 Rxe4 36. Rb3 Re8 37. Bf3 Bf2 38. Bg4 Qg6 39. Rxb6 fxg4 40. Qxg6+ Kxg6 41. Rxd6+ Kf7 42. Ng3 Re1 43. Bd2 Rg1 44. Rf6+ Kxf6 45. Ne4+ Kf7 46. Nxf2 Ra1 47. hxg4 Ra2 48. Be3 Bxg4 49. Kg3 Bf5 50. Bxc5 Ra5 0-1

