1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 c5 4. d5 exd5 5. cxd5 d6 6. Nc3 g6 7. g3 Bg7 8. Bg2 O-O 9. O-O Re8 10. Re1 $5 {A rare choice by White. Just like 10.h3 and 10.a4, this is a useful waiting move.} a6 11. a4 Nbd7 12. Bf4 ({No better is} 12. Nd2 $6 Rb8 13. Nc4 (13. a5 b5 14. axb6 Nxb6 15. Nb3 $2 (15. e4 Ng4 $3 $15 16. h3 Ne5 17. Bf1 (17. Qc2 c4 $17 18. Bf1 Nbd7 19. f4 Nd3 20. Bxd3 cxd3 21. Qxd3 Nc5 22. Qc2 Bxh3 $19) 17... c4 $1 $15 18. Na4 Nxa4 19. Qxa4 Bd7 ({Or} 19... f5 $36) 20. Qxa6 Bb5 $15) 15... Nc4 16. Ra2 Ng4 $17) 13... Ne5 14. Nxe5 Rxe5 15. Bf4 Re8 $15 16. a5 (16. Qd2 b5) 16... b5 17. axb6 Rxb6 18. Qc2 Ng4 $36 (18... h5 19. h3 Rb4 $36)) 12... Ng4 $1 {With two white minor pieces blocking the f2-pawn, this is the perfect moment for a knight maneuvre to e5.} 13. h3 (13. Bxd6 $2 Qb6 14. Bf4 c4 $3 15. e3 Qxb2 16. Ne2 Qxa1 $17) (13. e4 Nde5 14. h3 Nxf3+ 15. Bxf3 Ne5 16. Bg2 Rb8 ({Also good is} 16... c4) 17. a5 b5 18. axb6 Rxb6 19. Qc2 Rb4 ({Again,} 19... c4 {is a good alternative.})) 13... Nge5 14. Nd2 $6 (14. Ne4 Qe7 $132 {would have led to a dynamically balanced situation.} (14... Nxf3+ $2 15. exf3 $3 $16 Ne5 16. g4 $3)) 14... Rb8 ({Even better was} 14... g5 $3 15. Be3 f5 $15 16. a5 {, but} Qf6 $1 {, and Black has the initiative.} ({And now not} 16... b5 $2 17. axb6 Nxb6 18. Nf3 ({or} 18. Nb3))) 15. Nce4 Qc7 16. Qc2 b5 17. axb5 axb5 $15 18. b4 c4 $6 (18... Bb7 $15) 19. Nc3 Nf6 20. Ra5 Nd3 21. Rea1 Nxf4 22. gxf4 Nh5 23. e3 Bf5 24. Qc1 Qc8 25. Kh2 g5 26. Rxb5 gxf4 27. e4 Bd7 28. Rxb8 Qxb8 29. Rb1 Qa7 30. Nd1 c3 31. Nc4 Qa2 32. Nxd6 c2 33. Rb2 cxd1=Q 34. Qxd1 Qxb2 35. Nxe8 Be5 36. Qxh5 f3+ 37. Kg1 Qb1+ 38. Bf1 Bb5 39. Kh1 Qxf1# 0-1

