1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 c5 4. d5 d6 5. Nc3 exd5 6. cxd5 g6 7. g3 Bg7 8. Bg2 O-O 9. O-O Nbd7 $5 10. Re1 $5 ({The main move here is} 10. Bf4 {, and after} Qe7 {, both sides have various options:} 11. Re1 (11. a4 Ng4 $132 (11... h6 $132)) (11. h3 h6 $132) 11... Ng4 $132 12. e4 (12. a4 Nge5 $1 (12... Nde5 $6 13. h3 Nxf3+ 14. exf3 Ne5 15. Bxe5 $16 dxe5 16. f4) 13. Qc2 b6 14. a5 Ba6 15. axb6 axb6 $132) 12... Nde5 $132 13. h3 Nxf3+ 14. Qxf3 Ne5 15. Qe2 Bd7) 10... Ng4 {A good move, but again, Black has several alternatives.} (10... Re8 $5) (10... h6 $5) 11. h3 Nge5 $132 12. Nd2 {Threatening to win the knight with f2-f4.} (12. Nxe5 Nxe5 13. f4 {is harmless:} Nc4 14. e4 b5 {, and Black's position is already preferable.}) 12... f5 13. f4 Nf7 14. e4 fxe4 15. Ndxe4 {The knight on f7 fulfills very important defensive tasks, protecting d6 and preventing Ne4-g5-e6.} a6 16. a4 Rb8 17. Be3 $2 ({Correct was} 17. a5 Nf6 (17... b5 18. axb6 Rxb6 $132) 18. Nxf6+ Bxf6 19. Ne4 Bd4+ 20. Kh2 Bf5 $13) 17... b5 $15 18. axb5 axb5 19. Bf2 b4 20. Na4 Bb7 21. Nd2 Ra8 22. Nc4 Ba6 23. Bf1 g5 $3 $17 24. Re6 Bxc4 $1 25. Bxc4 gxf4 26. gxf4 Nh6 $6 (26... Nfe5 $3 27. fxe5 Nxe5 $19) 27. Qd2 Nf5 28. Bb5 Nb6 29. Kh1 Kh8 30. Ree1 Nxa4 31. Rxa4 Rxa4 32. Bxa4 Qf6 $1 $19 33. Re2 Qh6 34. Kh2 Nd4 $6 (34... Nh4 $1 35. Bxh4 Qxh4 36. b3 Bh6) (34... c4 $5) 35. Bxd4 Bxd4 36. b3 Rg8 $2 (36... Qh5 {was still winning:} 37. Bc6 Qf3 38. Bd7 Qxb3) 37. Rg2 Rxg2+ 38. Kxg2 Qg6+ 39. Kf3 $17 {White defended this unpleasant position very well and fully deserved the shared point in the end.} Qf5 40. Kg3 Qg6+ 41. Kf3 Qf7 42. Kg3 Qxd5 43. Qe2 Bf6 44. Qf3 Qd4 45. Bc6 Qg1+ 46. Qg2 Qe3+ 47. Qf3 Qe1+ 48. Kg4 Qe6+ $6 49. Kg3 Bd4 50. Bd5 Qe1+ 51. Kg4 c4 52. Bxc4 Qg1+ 53. Qg3 h5+ 54. Kf3 Qe3+ 55. Kg2 Qd2+ 56. Kh1 Qc1+ 1/2-1/2

