1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 e6 4. Nc3 exd5 5. cxd5 d6 6. Nf3 g6 7. Bf4 a6 8. e4 b5 9. Qe2 Be7 10. Qc2 O-O 11. a4 b4 12. Nd1 Re8 {Already here, instead of Re8, Black can go b3} (12... b3 13. Qb1 (13. Qxb3 Nxe4 {Black is doing very well}) 13... Nbd7 {With b3 we gave away the c3 square for the Nd1, but we gained the b4 square in return} 14. Nc3 Re8 15. Bd3 Nh5 16. Be3 Bf6 17. O-O Rb8 $15 {[%cal Gd7e5]}) 13. Bd3 Nbd7 14. h3 Qc7 15. O-O Bf8 {Black spent too much time and White stabilized the position and he was better} 16. Ne3 b3 17. Qb1 Rb8 18. Nd2 Ne5 19. Be2 Rb4 20. Bg5 Bg7 21. f4 Ned7 22. e5 dxe5 23. f5 Bb7 24. Bc4 Rxc4 25. d6 Qxd6 26. Ndxc4 Qc7 27. fxg6 hxg6 28. Qd3 Ne4 29. Rxf7 Kxf7 30. Nd5 Qc6 31. Qxe4 Re6 32. Rf1+ Kg8 33. Rd1 Nb6 34. Na5 Qxd5 35. Rxd5 Bxd5 36. Qe3 c4 37. Qd2 Be4 38. Be3 Bd3 39. Nxb3 Nxa4 40. Qb4 1-0

