1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 c5 4. g3 cxd4 5. Nxd4 d5 6. Bg2 e5 7. Nf3 d4 8. O-O Nc6 9. e3 (9. Ne1 Be7 10. e4 {Ideas with e4 exist but Black is doing very well.} Bg4 {Provoking weaknesses} 11. Bf3 (11. f3 Be6 $17) 11... Be6 $17) 9... Be7 10. exd4 exd4 11. Bg5 O-O 12. Nbd2 Be6 (12... h6 {is the best move and Black is much better} 13. Bxf6 Bxf6 14. Ne4 Bf5 (14... Be7 {is also possible}) 15. Nxf6+ Qxf6 16. Re1 d3 17. Qd2 Rfe8 $17) 13. a3 a5 (13... h6 $1 {h6 is even better than a5 preventing b4. The queenside expansion is ineffective when the Nc6 can find a square to jump in the center} 14. Bxf6 Bxf6 15. b4 d3 16. Rb1 Re8 (16... Qd7 17. b5 Nd4 $19) 17. b5 Na5 $19) 14. b3 Bf5 (14... h6 {h6 was again possible} 15. Bxf6 Bxf6 16. Ne1 d3 $19) 15. Re1 h6 16. Bxf6 Bxf6 17. c5 (17. Ne4 d3 18. Ra2 Re8 19. Nxf6+ Qxf6 $19) 17... d3 18. Rb1 Ne7 (18... Qd7 19. Nc4 Rae8) 19. Ne4 Bxe4 20. Rxe4 Nd5 21. Qxd3 Nc3 22. Qc2 Nxb1 23. Qxb1 Qd7 24. Qc2 Rfd8 25. Bf1 Rac8 26. b4 b6 27. Kg2 axb4 28. axb4 bxc5 29. bxc5 Qc6 30. h4 Rd5 31. Rc4 h5 32. Bd3 Rxc5 33. Rxc5 Qxc5 34. Qe2 Rb8 35. Nd2 Qd5+ 36. Ne4 Bd4 37. Bc4 Qc6 38. Qd3 Rb4 39. Ba2 Kf8 40. Qf3 Qb7 41. Ng5 Qxf3+ 42. Kxf3 Bxf2 (42... Be5 43. Ne4 Bd6 44. Nxd6 Rd4 45. Kg2 Rxd6 46. Bc4 g6 47. f4 Rc6 48. Bb3 Rc3 49. Bd5 f5 50. Kg1 Rc2 51. Bb3 Rb2 52. Bd5 Ke7 53. Bc4 Kd6 54. Bf7) 43. Bxf7 Bxg3 44. Bxh5 Bxh4 45. Ne4 Ke7 46. Bg4 Bf6 47. Bf5 Be5 48. Bc8 g6 49. Bg4 Rb3+ 50. Ke2 Bd4 51. Nd2 Re3+ 52. Kf2 Rd3+ 53. Ke2 Rg3 54. Bf3 Ke6 55. Bb7 Kf5 56. Nf3 Bb6 57. Nh4+ Kg5 58. Ng2 Rc3 59. Be4 Rb3 60. Bc6 Kg4 0-1

