1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. g3 c5 4. Nf3 cxd4 5. Nxd4 d5 6. Bg2 e5 7. Nf3 d4 8. O-O Nc6 9. e3 Be7 10. exd4 exd4 11. Qb3 $6 O-O (11... Nd7 $1 {Black didn't use the Qb3 move properly and didn't go Nd7}) (11... Ne4 {This is playable with the same idea Nc5}) 12. Bg5 (12. Bf4 $6 Nd7 $3 {is even better now because we are threatening Nc5 but also g5 perhaps} 13. Nbd2 (13. Re1 Nc5 14. Qd1 Bf6 15. Ne5 Qb6 $15) 13... g5 $17) (12. a3 a5 13. Bg5 Nd7 14. Bxe7 Qxe7 15. Nbd2 Nc5 16. Qd1 Bg4) 12... h6 $1 13. Bxf6 Bxf6 14. Nbd2 Rb8 (14... Bf5 {[%cal Gd8d7]} 15. Qxb7 Rc8 $44) (14... Re8 {is also possible}) 15. Ne4 Be6 (15... Bf5 16. Nxf6+ Qxf6 $17) 16. Qa4 Be7 17. Rfd1 Bf5 18. Ne1 Re8 19. Nd3 (19. Nc2 d3 $17 {Usually, the complications tend to favor the player who has the isolated pawn - Black in our case} (19... Bf8 $1 $19 {This is winning, the move d3 shows what happens when the pawn is pushed and how the complications can be played out}) 20. Ne1 Ne5 21. Qb3 (21. f4 Qd4+ 22. Kh1 (22. Nf2 Ng4) 22... Bxe4) 21... Bg4 22. Rd2 Be2) 19... a6 20. Rac1 Bf8 21. Nec5 Bxc5 22. Nxc5 Re2 23. Qb3 Qf6 24. Bf3 d3 25. Bxc6 Qxc6 26. Nxd3 Qf3 0-1

